{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}} {{Use Indian English|date=November 2019}} {{Other uses}} {{cleanup|date=September 2014|reason=terrible capitalization and spacing}} <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Indian cities]] for details --> {{Infobox settlement | name = Bansi | native_name = | native_name_lang = | other_name = | nickname = | settlement_type = City | image_skyline = | image_alt = | image_caption = | pushpin_map = India Uttar Pradesh | pushpin_label_position = bottom | pushpin_map_alt = | pushpin_map_caption = Location in Uttar Pradesh, India | coordinates = {{coord|27|10|30|N|82|55|45|E|display=inline,title}} | subdivision_type = Country | subdivision_name = [[India]] | subdivision_type1 = [[States and territories of India|State]] | subdivision_name1 = [[Uttar Pradesh]] | subdivision_type2 = [[List of districts of India|District]] | subdivision_name2 = [[Siddharthnagar district|Siddharthnagar]] | established_title = <!-- Established --> | government_type = Democracy | unit_pref = Metric | elevation_m = 90 | population_total = 41,057 | population_as_of = 2011 | population_density_km2 = auto | demographics_type1 = Languages | demographics1_title1 = Official | demographics1_info1 = Hindi,Avadhi | timezone1 = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]] | utc_offset1 = +5:30 | postal_code_type = <!-- [[Postal Index Number|PIN]] --> | postal_code = 272153 | registration_plate = UP-55 | website = {{URL|http://sidharthnagar.nic.in}} }} '''Bansi''' is a city and a [[municipal board]] in [[Siddharthnagar district]] in the state of [[Uttar Pradesh]], India Bansi is situated on the bank of Rapti River in Siddharthnagar District. (not to be confused with [[Baansi]].
==Overview== {{Unreferenced section|date=May 2015}} The city of Bansi is situated at a distance of 52 kilometers from [[Basti, Uttar Pradesh|Basti]] and 90 kilometers from [[Gorakhpur, Uttar Pradesh|Gorakhpur]]. It was the first developed city of the [[Siddharthnagar district]]. Before [[Naugarh]] (Siddharthnagar) was declared as capital.
==Geography== Bansi was located at the bank of river [[West Rapti River|Rapti]] at {{Coord|27.17|N|82.93|E}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.co.in/maps/search/Siddharthnagar,+Uttar+Pradesh/@28.652225,77.097764,80268m/data=!3m1!4b1?authuser=0&source=s_q&authuser=0&hl=en&dg=dbrw&newdg=1|title=Google Maps|website=Google Maps|accessdate=1 February 2018}}</ref> It has an average elevation of 90 metres. Raja Ratansen Inter collage & Raja Ratansen Degree collage is hub of education in Bansi Assembly & It is situated at Bansi to Etwa Road Near Rapti River And Navodaya Vidyalay established at Basantpur. 3 to 4 kilimeter from Bansi town along bansi etwa Road.
==Demographics== As of [[2011 Indian Census]], Bansi Nagar Parishad had a total population of 41,057.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.citypopulation.de/php/india-uttarpradesh.php?cityid=0945404000|title=Bansi (Siddharthnagar, Uttar Pradesh, India) - Population Statistics, Charts, Map, Location, Weather and Web Information|website=Citypopulation.de|url-status=live|access-date=2 November 2019}}</ref> Males constituted 51% of the population(21,105) and females 49%(19,952). Bansi has an average literacy rate of 58%, lower than the national average of 59.5%; with 61% of the males and 39% of females literate. 18% of the population is under 6 years of age.There are total 6,152 House Holds in Bansi. Total number of workers in Bansi is 11,244 (27%). 7,395 are regular Workers and 3,849 are Irregular Workers.
==Travel and connectivity== Bansi is well connected to the nearby towns and cities. As it was the center of the activities and many government offices were located at Bansi, it has been well connected to the nearby towns. Roadways (UPSRTC) bus station as well as private bus stand is there. From Bansi regular buses to Siddharthnagar, Gorakhpur, Basti, Khalilabad and Domariyagunj are always available. Also buses to Lucknow, Kanpur, Allahabad, Ayodhyay, Faizabad, Akbarpur, Tanda, Rajesultanpur, Azamgarh and Delhi run daily many times from Bansi. Private buses and jeeps are also available for many nearing towns.The nearest railway station is Naugarh (Siddharthnagar). Basti is also one of the near railway stations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.roaddistance.in/trains/nearest-railway-station-to-bansi-uttar-pradesh.html|title=Nearest Railway Stations to Bansi Uttar Pradesh Uttar Pradesh , Nearby Railway Station & Closest Railway Station to Bansi Uttar Pradesh Uttar Pradesh|website=Roaddistance.in|url-status=live|access-date=2 November 2019}}</ref>& Now India Rail Minister Mr. Piyus Goyal announced between 2024 to 2025 from Khalilabad to Bahraich railway will be in operaton then Bansi city will get own Railway station.
